body:
https://github.com/libuv/libuv/blob/v1.x/test/test-tcp-close.c#L60

If you add an additional `ASSERT` test to this code:

```
static void write_cb(uv_write_t* req, int status) {
  /* write callbacks should run before the close callback */
  ASSERT(status == UV_ECANCELED);
  ASSERT(close_cb_called == 0);
  ASSERT(req->handle == (uv_stream_t*)&tcp_handle);
  write_cb_called++;
  free(req);
}
```

Then the following error occurs:

```
=============================================================
[%  22|+  61|-   0|T   0|S   1]: tcp_close
`tcp_close` failed: exit code 134
Output from process `tcp_close`:
Assertion failed in ../test/test-tcp-close.c on line 61: status == UV_ECANCELED
=============================================================
```

This is causing issues with an application we are developing with libuv where we are calling `uv_close` on two connections where one connection may have already called `uv_write` before it's callback is called and even though we are trying to handle `UV_ECANCELED` it appears libuv no longer supports "In-progress requests, like uv_connect_t or uv_write_t, are cancelled and have their callbacks called asynchronously with status=UV_ECANCELED."

Was this feature removed for `uv_write_t` or perhaps with the test not being present, was overlooked? Any chance we could please have `UV_ECANCELED` added in for `uv_write_t` callbacks when their tcp handle is `uv_close`.
